The budget being released today emphasizes fiscal responsibility, safety and security, equitable growth, and building a better America. The administration plans to reduce the federal deficit by over $1.3 trillion this year, cutting it in half compared to the previous administration. The strategy includes controlling the pandemic, growing the economy from the bottom up, and scaling back emergency spending. The budget aims to continue reducing the deficit, ensuring billionaires and large corporations pay their fair share. Investments will be made in securing communities, including more police, fighting gun crime, and crime prevention. The budget also includes one of the largest investments in national security, supporting Ukraine's needs, reducing costs for families, and advancing the Unity Agenda, which includes cutting child care and health care costs, ending cancer, supporting veterans, and improving mental health services. Overall, it is a budget focused on deficit reduction, security, and economic opportunity.